                  <div class="flex-fill">
                     <h2>STARTING USAGE FOR BAKING EMULSIONS:</h2>
                     <p>Flavor emulsions are water-soluble and highly concentrated flavors. For that reason, starting usage is 0.1% - 0.5%. by weight. Experimentation with flavor emulsions is needed. Feel free to call us for some tips when trying flavor emulsions for the first time in any of your culinary creations. When substituting flavor emulsions for flavoring extracts, use one teaspoon of baking emulsion for every one teaspoon of flavor extract. If the flavor of the added flavor emulsion to your baked good or beverage tastes good and dissipates after three to five seconds, it's perfect!</p>
                  </div>
               </div>
